  "author_association": "NONE",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "When using eth-endpoints, there can be situation when you need to restart your full node and it's running a bit late to catch-up with the highest block in eth1.\r\nThe thing is even though you can specify several end points, lighthouse seems to care only if node N is unreachable. If lighthouse can speak with the eth1 node, even being late of the synchronisation it doesn't use the fallback.\r\nIt would be great to force lighthouse to use endpoint N+1 until endpoint N is synced again?\r\n\r\n",
