    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Lighthouse should use the fallback as soon as the eth1 endpoint is unsynced AND \"far behind\". By \"far behind\" we mean that `remote_head_block.timestamp + ETH1_FOLLOW_DISTANCE / 2 * SECONDS_PER_ETH1_BLOCK < now`. Since we are only interested in the eth1 blocks before the `ETH1_FOLLOW_DISTANCE` this should be enough to ensure that we always get all blocks we need.\r\n\r\nIf you have witnessed a different behavior please post some logs, because that would be a bug.",
